bugs.suggestion:
Wrap each session usage in a try/finally block to ensure disposal:

```typescript
const { session } = await createAgentSession({ ... });
try {
  await session.prompt(schemaPrompt);
} finally {
  session.dispose();
}
```

Do this for both the schema and non-schema code paths.

Add a concurrency limit using a semaphore pattern or batching, or accept a `concurrency` option:

```typescript
const pipeline: PipelineFn = async (items, ...stages) => {
  // Process in batches of e.g. 4
  const concurrency = 4;
  // Use p-limit or manual batching
};
```

Append text blocks instead of overwriting, or accumulate across messages:

```typescript
for (const block of msg.content) {
  if (block.type === "text") {
    responseText += block.text;
  }
}
```

Or if you truly only want the last message's text, document this clearly.

Consider either re-throwing the error (with the step still updated), returning a discriminated result type like `{ ok: true, value } | { ok: false, error }`, or at minimum logging via `log()` before returning undefined:

```typescript
} catch (err: any) {
  step.status = "failed";
  step.completedAt = Date.now();
  step.error = err?.message ?? String(err);
  onStep(step);
  log(`Agent step "${step.name}" failed: ${step.error}`);
  return undefined;
}
```

Consider filtering out failed items from subsequent stages, or providing a sentinel value that stages can check:

```typescript
catch (err) {
  log(`Pipeline stage failed for item ${index}: ${err}`);
  return { _item: item, _result: undefined, _failed: true };
}
// Then filter before next stage:
const activeResults = results.filter(r => !r._failed);
```

